Job Description:
• Works with marketing managers to grow our audience and develop digital marketing plans (paid, owned, earned) for brand, marketing and communications campaigns for Urbanland and its projects;
• Sets up, manages and maintains digital platforms (eg websites, social media profiles, search engines, online travel agents, review sites, chatbots) across all projects, managing technical fixes to ensure functionality is running smoothly, content is on-brand, correct and up to date, etc;
• Implements online lead-generation and advertising activity to contribute towards achieving sales and leasing targets, including optimising return on advertising and marketing spend;
• Tracks analytics across all digital channels – create annual digital marketing audits; and analyse content, web and social media data weekly/monthly to report on progress and propose improvements;
• Designs digital marketing collateral (social media posts, videography, photography), works independently, with in-house designer or agency;
• Researches competitors and monitors their activity, analysing data to identify and define audiences
• Develops and cultivates relationships with KOLs and relevant influencers
• Assists to track overall advertising and project marketing budgets
• Keeps up to date with digital trends and developments to ensure Urbanland are at the forefront of innovation;
• Creates email marketing, SEO and SEM campaigns.

Job Requirement:
• Degree in business management; marketing management and other related fields;
• Minimum 3 years of work experience in digital marketing and/or communications-related roles;
• Proven good Experience with digital marketing planning and execution eg working on social media, content marketing, website development, creative production projects;
• Supported execution of a corporate marketing strategy and/or marketing campaign
• Good in verbal and written communication both English and Khmer;
• Computer literacy.

Job Description:
• Supports the execution of Chankiri, Urbanland and Treeline marketing strategies and tactics, on-going campaigns to amplify and build a strong recognition in Cambodia by working alongside the team to develop content and marketing materials for a variety of channels such as social media, content marketing, digital advertising, events, PR, outdoor advertising, community engagement, etc;
• Assists in project management for Chankiri, Urbanland and Treeline by coordinating among team and across departments in key activities initiatives, planning, budgeting and project teams’ roles and responsibilities to assure the project deliveries;
• Monitors, reports, and analyzes on the projects performance either by project/ by monthly and convert into the actionable items for the next month’s plan through reports and presentations;
• Supports the team to research and establish new connections online and offline (eg influencers, potential buyers, clients, key industry players, agencies, vendors etc), following up with stakeholders and organize meet-ups where required;
• Coordinates with external agencies and media channels on marketing and outreach efforts and liaise with PR and media contacts pre, during and post event;
• Collaborates with sales, product development, research teams, operation team (Treeline) and other relevant department to conduct up-to-date marketing campaigns reflecting the current sales performance, propose new initiatives if required and also conduct market research if needed;
• Supports the execution of customer experience improvement plans with sales and property management teams;
• Runs community engagement activities through physical and online events or groups eg potential and existing customers, clients, shoppers, industry members, exhibitions, CSR initiatives, etc;
• Plans and executes end-to-end event logistics and programming (pre, during and post event)
• Assists to track and evaluate performance of on/offline marketing activities and campaigns;
• Creates the standard operation process (SOP) or improve the current working flow and support general administration of the marketing department eg workshop set-ups, maintenance of standard operating procedures, expense reports, minute-taking, etc;
• Recommend any possible improvements or process enhancement to improve team performance;
• Performs as a liaison and work within the relevant designer and artist community on assigned Urbaland’s projects.

Job Requirement:
• Degree in business administration, marketing, media and communication, and other related fields;
• Minimum 02 years of work experience in marketing, preferable in real estate and construction industry;
• Proven good working experience in marketing project management, executing sales and/or marketing initiatives; marketing agencies, supplier for both online and offline media, digital marketing eg social media, media buys, content marketing, influencer relations;
• Experience in conducting market research and data analysis, event planning and execution;
• Proficient English communication both verbal and written;
• Computer and digital literacy.

